package compose:dynlink@0.1.0;

/// The uniform message endpoint that every dynamically-loadable
/// provider exports.
///
/// Runtime linking deliberately does NOT marshal typed WIT values
/// across the boundary (see `compose:host/invoker.call-with-cbor` for
/// the typed-CBOR approach, which this package supersedes). Instead a
/// provider exposes a single opaque method: the host forwards `payload`
/// bytes verbatim and never interprets them. The encoding is an
/// application concern; the recommended convention is a CBOR envelope
/// carrying a schema/version tag.
///
/// Because only bytes cross the boundary, resource handles never
/// transit and the nominal-resource type-identity problem that blocks
/// cross-instance typed linking does not arise. The cost is that there
/// is no host-side type checking: a malformed call surfaces as a
/// decoding error inside the guest, and providers must be written as
/// plugins that speak this contract.
interface endpoint {
  use sys:compose/types@1.0.0.{error};

  /// Handle one message. `method` selects an operation; `payload` is an
  /// opaque, application-encoded request body. The result is an opaque,
  /// application-encoded response body.
  handle: func(method: string, payload: list<u8>) -> result<list<u8>, error>;
}
